---
title: `$extend::state()`
description: Return the stored extension states if any, otherwise, return `$fail`.
...

~~~ .php.xmp
Extend::state($id, $key = null, $fail = false);
~~~

**Example:**

~~~ .php
$state = Extend::state('minify');
~~~

> **Note:** If `$key` is array, then it will become the alternate values of the `$state` output if some data are not available:
>
> ~~~ .php
> $state = Extend::state('minify', [
>     'html' => [2, 1] // add `html` property to `$state` if missing
> ]);
> ~~~

---

### Hooks

Key | Description
--- | -----------
`extend.state.{$id}` | Will affect the state output of extension with name `$id`.

> **Note:** `.` characters in `$id` will be converted into `\`.